<subSubSection pageId="182" pageNumber="183" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="182" pageNumber="183">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="182" pageNumber="183">
Weakly cushion-forming plant with a woody rootstock, from which arise ascending stems to 45 cm, vegetative parts pilose with somewhat stiff spreading hairs. Basal leaves 3-8 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.5-0.9 cm, oblong-oblanceolate, acute, entire, base long-attenuate and petiole-like up to 4 cm in length; stem leaves 2-5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.5-1 cm, oblanceolate to oblong, acute, entire, base cuneate to attenuate. Flowers in sessile (above) or shortly pedunculate (below) 2-3-flowered axillary heads; bracts usually &lt;3 cm long, lanceolate (if longer, than narrowly lanceolate); peduncles 0-1.5 cm; bracteoles 9-11 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1 mm, linear-oblong, acute, densely pilose; pedicels absent; outer sepals 9-11 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-2.5 mm, lanceolate, acuminate, densely pilose; inner sepals 8-9 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1 mm, linear-lanceolate; corolla 2-2.5 cm long, pink, shallowly lobed, midpetaline bands darker, adpressed pilose; ovary glabrous; style glabrous, divided 3 mm above base, stigmas 4.5-5 mm; capsule glabrous; seeds glabrous. [
<bibRefCitation author="Sa'ad, F" journalOrPublisher="Bronder Offset, Rotterdam" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" pagination="1 - 287" refId="B314" refString="Sa'ad, F, 1967. The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht. Bronder Offset, Rotterdam: 1 - 287" title="The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht" year="1967">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Sa’ad">Sa'ad</normalizedToken>
1967
</bibRefCitation>
: 162; 
<bibRefCitation author="Austin, DF" editor="Nasir, E" journalOrPublisher="Dept. of Botany, University of Karachi, Karachi" pageId="198" pageNumber="199" pagination="1 - 64" refId="B13" refString="Austin, DF, Ghazanfar, S, 1979. Convolvulaceae. In: Nasir, E, Ali, SI, Eds., Flora of Pakistan 126: Convolvulaceae. Dept. of Botany, University of Karachi, Karachi: 1 - 64" title="Convolvulaceae." volumeTitle="Flora of Pakistan 126: Convolvulaceae." year="1979">Austin and Ghazanfar 1979</bibRefCitation>
: 19]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
